        "text": "The exact SKF part number you should include on your PO is **6201-2RSH**. \n\nHere is a quick breakdown verifying how this part number meets your specifications:\n* **6201**: This base number identifies the standard series for a single-row deep groove ball bearing with a 12mm inner diameter (shaft), 32mm outer diameter, and 10mm width.\n* **-2RSH**: This is the SKF-specific suffix designating contacting rubber seals (made of NBR) on both sides of the bearing. *(Note: You may also see this listed under the older/alternative SKF suffix **6201-2RS1**, which is functionally identical)*.\n\nIf your application requires a stainless steel bearing rather than standard bearing steel, the correct SKU for the stainless variant is **W 6201-2RS1**. Otherwise, the standard **6201-2RSH** is the exact orderable part number you need.",
