    {
      "query": "Our progressive lubrication system requires a replacement SKF Lincoln electrically operated 24V DC pump capable of driving up to three pump elements. What is the base SKF Lincoln model number for this compact pump series so we don't accidentally order a hydraulic tool lubricator?",
      "agent": {
        "text": "The base SKF Lincoln model number you are looking for is the **P203** (part of the Quicklub family). \n\nThe P203 is a versatile, compact, electrically operated 24V DC pump explicitly designed for progressive lubrication systems. It features a built-in motor and reservoir, and it allows you to install up to three separate pump elements to drive your primary metering devices. \n\n**Note on newer models:** SKF is currently transitioning from the classic P203 to the newer **PLP** (Progressive Lubrication Pump) series. The PLP shares the same dimensions, mounting patterns, and 3-element capacity but features updated smart connectivity. Ordering a **P203** or **PLP** base model guarantees you are getting the correct electrical progressive pump. \n\nTo ensure you do not accidentally order a hydraulic tool lubricator (which are driven by machine hydraulics rather than a 24V DC electric motor, such as the Lincoln HTL series), strictly use the **P203** or **PLP** prefix. When building your final SKU, confirm the configuration code specifies a 24V DC motor, your required reservoir size, and the correct number of K-series pump elements (e.g., K5, K6, or K7).",
        "sources": [
